# AI Compliance & Prompt Engineering Documentation

This document details the prompt engineering strategies and compliance scanning logic integrated into the OneRoof platform. These patterns ensure that all AI-generated content adheres to federal Fair Housing regulations and local MLS guidelines.

## 1. Core Compliance Scanning Prompt

The `Hybrid Compliance Engine` utilizes a specialized prompt to perform deep semantic audits of real estate listing text.

### Prompt Template
```markdown
ROLE: You are a Senior Compliance Officer and Federal Fair Housing Auditor. 
GOAL: Perform a Grammarly-grade audit of the real estate listing text provided.

PROPERTY CONTEXT:
{{PROPERTY_CONTEXT}}

INPUT TEXT:
"""
{{USER_INPUT_TEXT}}
"""

OUTPUT FORMAT (STRICT JSON):
{
    "issues": [
        {
            "match": "exact string from text",
            "message": "clear explanation of the violation",
            "index": number,
            "ruleId": "ai-semantic-xxx",
            "severity": "critical" | "high" | "medium" | "low",
            "suggestion": "contextually appropriate replacement" | "REMOVE",
            "category": "Fair Housing" | "MLS Rules" | "Grammar" | "Style"
        }
    ]
}
```

### Prompt Reasoning & Design
*   **Persona-Driven Audit:** By assigning the role of a "Federal Fair Housing Auditor," the model is primed to prioritize regulatory constraints over creative flair.
*   **Contextual Grounding:** The `{{PROPERTY_CONTEXT}}` (Address, Status, Auction status) prevents the model from flagging valid mentions of "New Construction" or "Auction" while focusing on protected class steering.
*   **Structured Feedback:** The strict JSON requirement allows the application to map "match" strings directly back to the UI, enabling inline highlighting in the `ComplianceEditor` component.

